-- South Korea, U.S. Said to Reach Accord on Revising Pending Free-Trade Pact
-- B y   M a r k   D r a j e m
-- 2010-12-03T17:58:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/south-korea-u-s-said-to-reach-accord-on-revising-pending-free-trade-pact.html
The U.S. and South Korea reached
agreement on revising a pending free-trade agreement, including
a phase-out of auto tariffs over five years, according to a
person briefed on the negotiations.  The two sides wrapped up meetings today in Columbia,
Maryland, with U.S. Trade Representative Ron Kirk saying
“substantial progress” has been made during the talks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Drajem in Washington at 
 mdrajem@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
